{{Infobox power station | name = Coega Wind Farm | name_official = | image = Coega wind turbine-001.JPG | image_size = | image_caption = [[Wind turbine]] developed by {{Interlanguage link multi|Electrawinds|nl}} of [[Belgium]] | image_alt = | location_map = South Africa | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|33.7544812|S|25.6765536|E|type:landmark_dim:20km_region:ZA|display=inline,title}} | country = South Africa | location = [[Coega]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = 2010 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = Electrawind | operator = | ps_units_manu_model = [[General Electric]]: [[GE Wind Energy#GE 2.5MW|GE2.5XL]] 1.8&nbsp;MW | wind_hub_height = | wind_rotor_diameter = | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = | wind_site_elevation = | wind_site_usage = | wind_site_area = | ps_electrical_capacity = | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Coega Wind Farm''' is a [[wind farm]] in [[Coega]], an Industrial Development Zone (IDZ) covering {{convert|110|km2|abbr=on}} of land,<ref>[http://www.coega.co.za/content.asp?id=190&node0id=163 Coega Development Corporation :About Coega<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070203222854/http://www.coega.co.za/content.asp?id=190&node0id=163 |date=February 3, 2007 }}</ref> that is situated within the [[Nelson Mandela Metropolitan Municipality]] near [[Port Elizabeth]], in the [[Eastern Cape]] province of [[South Africa]]. Installed by the [[Belgium|Belgian]] company {{Interlanguage link multi|Electrawinds|nl}}, it was the first commercial wind farm built in the country.<ref name="coega-first-turbine">{{cite web|url=http://news.za.msn.com/economic/article.aspx?cp-documentid=153362721|title=Electrawinds launches 1st wind turbine at Coega|publisher=[[MSN]]|accessdate=13 May 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708225010/http://news.za.msn.com/economic/article.aspx?cp-documentid=153362721|archivedate=8 July 2011|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Development of a 57.5MW Wind Energy Project|url=http://publicprocess.co.za/index2.php?option=com_docman&task=doc_view&gid=507&Itemid=29|publisher=Public Process Consultants|accessdate=9 October 2010}}</ref>
