{{Infobox protected area | name = Rāzna National Park | alt_name = | iucn_category = II | photo = Вид с Маконькальнса-1.jpg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = View from Mākoņkalns hill to [[Lake Rāzna]] | photo_width = | map = Latvia | map_alt = | map_caption = Map of [[Latvia]] | map_width = | location = [[Latgale]], [[Latvia]] | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coord|56|16|N|27|30|E|region:LV|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <!-- kolossus-dewiki --> | area = {{Convert|532|km2|abbr=on}} | established = 2007 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = | world_heritage_site = | url = }} '''Rāzna National Park''' ({{lang-lv|Rāznas nacionālais parks}}) is a [[national park]] in the [[Latgale]] region of [[Latvia]]. It was established in 2007 and covers an area of {{Convert|532|km2|abbr=on}}. The initiative to create the Rāzna National Park out of an already existing nature park came from the [[Daugavpils University]].
This national park was created to protect [[Lake Rāzna]], the second largest [[lake]] in Latvia, and the surrounding areas. Because of this, 14% of the surface area of the national park consists of water surfaces. Valuable ecosystems - natural deciduous forests with many rare species of plants are found on several of the 26 islands in Ežezers lake. Of high value are also the semi-natural grasslands.
